                <h1>Understanding Poverty Background: Breaking the Cycle</h1>
                <p>Poverty background refers to the socioeconomic conditions that often inhibit individuals and families from achieving upward mobility. These conditions include lack of access to quality education, healthcare, and employment opportunities. Poverty can create a cycle that is challenging to break, perpetuating systemic inequalities across generations.</p>
